<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-14T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-14T06:00:00-05:00" n="625" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/6302: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-14T14:00:00+03:00">June 14,
                                1944—2 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received June 15—7:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2142. Department’s 1470, June 10, 6 p.m., regarding proposals of War Refugee
                        Board. The Embassy has addressed a letter to Vyshinski dated May 14
                        communicating the text of the statement of the Senate Foreign Relations
                        Committee and renewing its requests that the Soviet Government associate
                        itself with the President’s declaration of March 24. The letter also
                        requests that Soviet radio <pb facs="1084" n="1070" xml:id="pg_1070"/>
                        stations broadcast appropriate messages to Germany and German satellite
                        countries and that the Soviet radio messages be supplemented by
                        leaflets.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>